cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes an unsupervised deep learning approach, which involves optimizing a model, indicating that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of videos, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper involves learning tracklet associations and cross-camera tracklet correlation, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with re-identification, which is a security-related problem, suggesting that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
